body:
I cannot identify the bug and did not find a way to reproduce on psalm.dev as I cannot compose the same environment there.

Given this example https://psalm.dev/r/ffc95878b1 in a namespace `N\A` from `vendor` and then running in namespace `N\B`

```php
namespace N\B;

use N\A\FormatImpl;
use function N\A\run;

run(new FormatImpl);
```

gives somethingl like  
> Argument 1 of N\A run expects N\A\Format<N\A\Output>, N\A\FormatImpl provided run(new FormatImpl);

Running the same code in vendor's `N\A` works as expected though.

-------------------

I reproduced it in two repos with identical code. One throws error and the other one does not.

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

// Either one of these:
// namespace SimPod\PsalmBugs\Bug;
// namespace SimPod\ClickHouseClient\Bug;

use SimPod\ClickHouseClient\Client\ClickHouseClient;
use SimPod\ClickHouseClient\Format\JsonEachRow;

final class First
{
    public function exec(ClickHouseClient $clickHouseClient) : void
    {
        $clickHouseClient->selectWithParameters('s', [], new JsonEachRow());
    }
}
```

Here it throws:

https://github.com/simPod/PsalmBugs/blob/generics-library/src/Bug/First.php

```sh
$ vendor/bin/psalm
Scanning files...
Analyzing files...

E

ERROR: InvalidArgument - src/Bug/First.php:14:58 - Argument 3 of SimPod\ClickHouseClient\Client\ClickHouseClient::selectWithParameters expects SimPod\ClickHouseClient\Format\Format<SimPod\ClickHouseClient\Output\Output>, SimPod\ClickHouseClient\Format\JsonEachRow provided
        $clickHouseClient->selectWithParameters('s', [], new JsonEachRow());


------------------------------
1 errors found
------------------------------

Checks took 0.51 seconds and used 146.212MB of memory
Psalm was able to infer types for 100% of the codebase
```

The same thing works as expected here:

https://github.com/simPod/PhpClickHouseClient/blob/psalm-bug/src/Bug/First.php

```
$ vendor/bin/psalm
Scanning files...
Analyzing files...

░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░

------------------------------
No errors found!
------------------------------

Checks took 1.08 seconds and used 217.895MB of memory
Psalm was able to infer types for 99.2806% of the codebase
```

Am I doing something wrong or is it a bug? Thanks!
